      "message": "Patch Set 6: Code-Review+1\n\nThanks for the explanations.\nAs you say, LNET_PEER_RTR_DISCOVERY is only set in this code, and this code is only called by lnet_monitor_thread(), which is single threaded.  So there can be no race w.r.t setting the flag, so testing it inside the lock is unnecessary.  I would prefer the commit message explained that, but I guess it is no big deal.\n\nHowever - now that I understand the code a bit better and have read it again, I see that each call will only ping one local interface for each router.  So it needs to be called multiple times per ping interval is there are multiple local interfaces that connect to the same router.  Can that happen?  Might that be why the division was there before? (We have the same division in lnet_monitor_thread().  Maybe that is sufficient).\n\nIt would be clearer if lnet_check_routers() checked every local interface on every router, pinged all that were ready, and returned the time until the next one would be ready.  But that should really be a separate patch.\nAnd ... that wouldn't work as the use of  ->lp_disc_net_id means that you can only ping one net on a router at a time..",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
